dct_description_sm: From various Admiralty surveys between 1945 and 1925; adjusted to the triangulation by Commander W.U. Moore, H.M. Surveying Ship "Rambler," 1886-7 ; The inland features are from Sketch Surveys by Rev. W. Riddel, M.D. assisted by Rev. J.C. Gibson, D.D., Rev. W. Ashmore and Dr. P.B. Cousland, 1899 ; Published at the Admiralty, 28th Novr. 1890, under the Superintendence of Captail W.J.L. Wharton, R.N.: F.R.S. Hydrographer ; Engraved by Davies & Company ; Reproduced by the U.S. Hydrographic Office...
Depths shown by soundings; relief by hachures and spot heights.
2 inset charts, 2 profile views, Currents note.
"Emergency reproduction of B.A. chart - Oct. 1937; Mar. 1943."
Shows low water areas, drainage, islands, towns, buildings.
Descriptive text ("fishing stakes," "highly cultivated plain well watered by branches of the River Han").
dct_creator_sm: Wharton, W. J. L. (William James Lloyd), 1843-1905
